│ CreateInsertElement (emits insertelement or insert_subvector) with subsequent │
│ CreateShuffle. The code paths around line ~16055 call createInsertVector when │
│ Scalar is a fixed vector type, capturing the intrinsic and then later         │
│ building shuffles. If insertion points differ or the intrinsic ends up in a   │
│ block with tighter scope than its uses, dominance breaks.\n\n3. Root Cause    │
│ Analysis:\nThe core issue is the use of llvm.vector.insert (insert_subvector) │
